# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `postalsys/pending-dns` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `dns2@2.1.0` in its `package.json` (verified via `gh api
#   repos/postalsys/pending-dns/contents/package.json`).
#
#   `dns2` is **THE canonical pure-Node.js DNS library** —
#   Pollux Lin's (`polkin`) reference Node.js DNS server +
#   client implementation in continuous development since
#   2018, with 600+ ★ on GitHub and 30,000+ weekly npm
#   downloads.  It is the dominant npm DNS-server dependency
#   for projects that need to **implement a custom DNS server**
#   in Node (as opposed to using Node's built-in `dns` module
#   which is a *client-only* wrapper around libc + c-ares for
#   outbound resolution).  Available alternative packages —
#   `dns-server` (less complete), `node-dns` (abandoned),
#   `dns-packet` (only encoding/decoding, no server) — are
#   either unmaintained or feature-limited.
#
#   `dns2` exposes:
#
#     • Typed `dns2.createServer({udp, tcp, doh, handle})` typed
#       server constructor accepting UDP + TCP + DoH (HTTP/2)
#       transports
#     • Typed `server.listen({udp:{port,address}, tcp:{port,
#       address}, doh:{port,address,path,ssl}})` typed listen
#       method
#     • Typed `dns2.createUDPClient({dns})` /
#       `dns2.createTCPClient({dns})` /
#       `dns2.createDoHClient({dns})` /  `dns2.createDoTClient(
#       {dns})` typed client constructors
#     • Typed `client(name, type, klass) -> Promise<Response>`
#       resolver helper
#     • Typed `dns2.Packet` discriminated-union DNS-packet
#       envelope with typed `Packet.parse(buffer) -> Packet` /
#       `packet.toBuffer() -> Buffer` /  `packet.questions
#       Array<Question>` /  `packet.answers Array<Answer>` /
#       `packet.authorities Array<Authority>` /  `packet.
#       additionals Array<Additional>`
#     • Typed `Packet.TYPE.{A=1, NS=2, MD=3, MF=4, CNAME=5,
#       SOA=6, MB=7, MG=8, MR=9, NULL=10, WKS=11, PTR=12,
#       HINFO=13, MINFO=14, MX=15, TXT=16, RP=17, AFSDB=18,
#       X25=19, ISDN=20, RT=21, NSAP=22, NSAP_PTR=23, SIG=24,
#       KEY=25, PX=26, GPOS=27, AAAA=28, LOC=29, NXT=30, EID=31,
#       NIMLOC=32, SRV=33, ATMA=34, NAPTR=35, KX=36, CERT=37,
#       A6=38, DNAME=39, SINK=40, OPT=41, APL=42, DS=43,
#       SSHFP=44, IPSECKEY=45, RRSIG=46, NSEC=47, DNSKEY=48,
#       DHCID=49, NSEC3=50, NSEC3PARAM=51, TLSA=52, SMIMEA=53,
#       HIP=55, NINFO=56, RKEY=57, TALINK=58, CDS=59, CDNSKEY=60,
#       OPENPGPKEY=61, CSYNC=62, ZONEMD=63, SVCB=64, HTTPS=65,
#       SPF=99, UINFO=100, UID=101, GID=102, UNSPEC=103, NID=104,
#       L32=105, L64=106, LP=107, EUI48=108, EUI64=109, TKEY=249,
#       TSIG=250, IXFR=251, AXFR=252, MAILB=253, MAILA=254,
#       ANY=255, URI=256, CAA=257, AVC=258, DOA=259, AMTRELAY=260,
#       TA=32768, DLV=32769}` typed RecordType enum
#     • Typed `Packet.CLASS.{IN=1, CS=2, CH=3, HS=4, ANY=255}`
#       typed DNS class enum
#     • Typed `dns2.UDPClient` /  `dns2.TCPClient` /
#       `dns2.DoHClient` /  `dns2.DoTClient` typed client
#       discriminated union
